  "prompt": "What I can do now because my 18 year will be completed in 17 January 2017. and most companies age limit is 18 year as on aug 2016?",
  "response": "If you are looking to apply for jobs or internships with the requirement that candidates be 18 years old by August 2016, you would not meet that criteria since your 18th birthday is in January 2017. However, you still have several options:\n\n1. **Seek Opportunities Without Age Restrictions:** Look for job positions, internships, and volunteer opportunities that do not have strict age requirements.\n\n2. **Gain Experience:** Engage in activities that can enhance your resume, such as volunteering, online courses, certifications, or freelance work. These experiences can make you a more competitive candidate when you become eligible for those positions.\n\n3. **Networking:** Connect with professionals in your desired industry. Networking can sometimes lead to opportunities that are not publicly advertised and may not have formal age restrictions.\n\n4. **Education:** Focus on continuing your education, whether through high school completion, college enrollment, or additional coursework relevant to your career interests.\n\n5. **Prepare for Future Applications:** Once you turn 18, you will be eligible to apply for the positions you mentioned. In the meantime, you can prepare your application materials, such as your resume, cover letter, and any required documentation, so you are ready to apply when the time comes.\n\nRemember, while age can be a limiting factor in certain situations, there are many other ways to build valuable skills and experience that can help you in your career aspirations.",
